  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: 51ee3e37f5ded7941ab6216610f6fc67, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - title: Greetings from Paul
      content: "  This letter is from Paul, chosen by the will of God to be an apostle
        of Christ Jesus, and from our brother Timothy.I am writing to God\u2019s
        church in Corinth and to all of his holy people throughout Greece.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:1 '
        content: Greek <b>Achaia, </b>the southern region of the Greek peninsula.
    - title: God Offers Comfort to All
      content: 'May God our Father and the Lord Jesus Christ give you grace and peace.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'All praise to God, the Father of our Lord Jesus Christ. God is our
        merciful Father and the source of all comfort. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'He comforts us in all our troubles so that we can comfort others.
        When they are troubled, we will be able to give them the same comfort God
        has given us. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the more we suffer for Christ, the more God will shower us with
        his comfort through Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Even when we are weighed down with troubles, it is for your comfort
        and salvation! For when we ourselves are comforted, we will certainly comfort
        you. Then you can patiently endure the same things we suffer. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are confident that as you share in our sufferings, you will also
        share in the comfort God gives us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We think you ought to know, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        about the trouble we went through in the province of Asia. We were crushed
        and overwhelmed beyond our ability to endure, and we thought we would never
        live through it. '
      comments:
      - number: '1:8 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'In fact, we expected to die. But as a result, we stopped relying
        on ourselves and learned to rely only on God, who raises the dead. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And he did rescue us from mortal danger, and he will rescue us again.
        We have placed our confidence in him, and he will continue to rescue us. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Change of Plans"
      content: 'And you are helping us by praying for us. Then many people will give
        thanks because God has graciously answered so many prayers for our safety.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We can say with confidence and a clear conscience that we have lived
        with a God-given holiness[[COMMENT(0)]] and sincerity in all our dealings.
        We have depended on God\u2019s grace, not on our own human wisdom. That is
        how we have conducted ourselves before the world, and especially toward you. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:12 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>honesty.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Our letters have been straightforward, and there is nothing written
        between the lines and nothing you can\u2019t understand. I hope someday you
        will fully understand us, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "even if you don\u2019t understand us now. Then on the day when the
        Lord Jesus[[COMMENT(0)]] returns, you will be proud of us in the same way
        we are proud of you.  "
      comments:
      - number: '1:14 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>our Lord Jesus.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Since I was so sure of your understanding and trust, I wanted to
        give you a double blessing by visiting you twice\u2014 "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'first on my way to Macedonia and again when I returned from Macedonia.[[COMMENT(0)]]
        Then you could send me on my way to Judea.  '
      comments:
      - number: '1:16 '
        content: <b>Macedonia </b>was in the northern region of Greece.
    - title: 
      content: "You may be asking why I changed my plan. Do you think I make my plans
        carelessly? Do you think I am like people of the world who say \u201CYes\u201D
        when they really mean \u201CNo\u201D? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As surely as God is faithful, our word to you does not waver between
        \u201CYes\u201D and \u201CNo.\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For Jesus Christ, the Son of God, does not waver between \u201CYes\u201D
        and \u201CNo.\u201D He is the one whom Silas,[[COMMENT(0)]] Timothy, and
        I preached to you, and as God\u2019s ultimate \u201CYes,\u201D he always
        does what he says. "
      comments:
      - number: '1:19 '
        content: Greek <b>Silvanus.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "For all of God\u2019s promises have been fulfilled in Christ with
        a resounding \u201CYes!\u201D And through Christ, our \u201CAmen\u201D (which
        means \u201CYes\u201D) ascends to God for his glory.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is God who enables us, along with you, to stand firm for Christ.
        He has commissioned us, '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'and he has identified us as his own by placing the Holy Spirit in
        our hearts as the first installment that guarantees everything he has promised
        us.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now I call upon God as my witness that I am telling the truth. The
        reason I didn\u2019t return to Corinth was to spare you from a severe rebuke. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  So I decided that I would not bring you grief with another painful
        visit. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For if I cause you grief, who will make me glad? Certainly not someone
        I have grieved. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "That is why I wrote to you as I did, so that when I do come, I won\u2019t
        be grieved by the very ones who ought to give me the greatest joy. Surely
        you all know that my joy comes from your being joyful. "
      comments: []
    - title: Forgiveness for the Sinner
      content: "I wrote that letter in great anguish, with a troubled heart and many
        tears. I didn\u2019t want to grieve you, but I wanted to let you know how
        much love I have for you.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am not overstating it when I say that the man who caused all the
        trouble hurt all of you more than he hurt me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Most of you opposed him, and that was punishment enough. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now, however, it is time to forgive and comfort him. Otherwise he
        may be overcome by discouragement. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I urge you now to reaffirm your love for him.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I wrote to you as I did to test you and see if you would fully comply
        with my instructions. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When you forgive this man, I forgive him, too. And when I forgive
        whatever needs to be forgiven, I do so with Christ\u2019s authority for your
        benefit, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'so that Satan will not outsmart us. For we are familiar with his
        evil schemes.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When I came to the city of Troas to preach the Good News of Christ,
        the Lord opened a door of opportunity for me. '
      comments: []
    - title: Ministers of the New Covenant
      content: "But I had no peace of mind because my dear brother Titus hadn\u2019t
        yet arrived with a report from you. So I said good-bye and went on to Macedonia
        to find him.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But thank God! He has made us his captives and continues to lead
        us along in Christ\u2019s triumphal procession. Now he uses us to spread
        the knowledge of Christ everywhere, like a sweet perfume. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our lives are a Christ-like fragrance rising up to God. But this
        fragrance is perceived differently by those who are being saved and by those
        who are perishing. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'To those who are perishing, we are a dreadful smell of death and
        doom. But to those who are being saved, we are a life-giving perfume. And
        who is adequate for such a task as this?  '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Are we beginning to praise ourselves again? Are we like others,
        who need to bring you letters of recommendation, or who ask you to write
        such letters on their behalf? Surely not! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The only letter of recommendation we need is you yourselves. Your
        lives are a letter written in our[[COMMENT(0)]] hearts; everyone can read
        it and recognize our good work among you. '
      comments:
      - number: '3:2 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>your.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "Clearly, you are a letter from Christ showing the result of our ministry
        among you. This \u201Cletter\u201D is written not with pen and ink, but with
        the Spirit of the living God. It is carved not on tablets of stone, but on
        human hearts.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are confident of all this because of our great trust in God through
        Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'It is not that we think we are qualified to do anything on our own.
        Our qualification comes from God. '
      comments: []
    - title: The Glory of the New Covenant
      content: 'He has enabled us to be ministers of his new covenant. This is a
        covenant not of written laws, but of the Spirit. The old written covenant
        ends in death; but under the new covenant, the Spirit gives life.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "The old way,[[COMMENT(0)]] with laws etched in stone, led to death,
        though it began with such glory that the people of Israel could not bear
        to look at Moses\u2019 face. For his face shone with the glory of God, even
        though the brightness was already fading away. "
      comments:
      - number: '3:7 '
        content: Or <b>ministry; </b>also in 3:8, 9, 10, 11, 12.
    - title: 
      content: "Shouldn\u2019t we expect far greater glory under the new way, now
        that the Holy Spirit is giving life? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If the old way, which brings condemnation, was glorious, how much
        more glorious is the new way, which makes us right with God! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In fact, that first glory was not glorious at all compared with the
        overwhelming glory of the new way. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So if the old way, which has been replaced, was glorious, how much
        more glorious is the new, which remains forever!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Since this new way gives us such confidence, we can be very bold. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are not like Moses, who put a veil over his face so the people
        of Israel would not see the glory, even though it was destined to fade away. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But the people\u2019s minds were hardened, and to this day whenever
        the old covenant is being read, the same veil covers their minds so they
        cannot understand the truth. And this veil can be removed only by believing
        in Christ. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Yes, even today when they read Moses\u2019 writings, their hearts
        are covered with that veil, and they do not understand.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But whenever someone turns to the Lord, the veil is taken away. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For the Lord is the Spirit, and wherever the Spirit of the Lord is,
        there is freedom. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Treasure in Fragile Clay Jars
      content: '  Therefore, since God in his mercy has given us this new way,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        we never give up. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:1 '
        content: Or <b>ministry.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "We reject all shameful deeds and underhanded methods. We don\u2019t
        try to trick anyone or distort the word of God. We tell the truth before
        God, and all who are honest know this.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If the Good News we preach is hidden behind a veil, it is hidden
        only from people who are perishing. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Satan, who is the god of this world, has blinded the minds of those
        who don\u2019t believe. They are unable to see the glorious light of the
        Good News. They don\u2019t understand this message about the glory of Christ,
        who is the exact likeness of God.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You see, we don\u2019t go around preaching about ourselves. We preach
        that Jesus Christ is Lord, and we ourselves are your servants for Jesus\u2019
        sake. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For God, who said, \u201CLet there be light in the darkness,\u201D
        has made this light shine in our hearts so we could know the glory of God
        that is seen in the face of Jesus Christ.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We now have this light shining in our hearts, but we ourselves are
        like fragile clay jars containing this great treasure.[[COMMENT(0)]] This
        makes it clear that our great power is from God, not from ourselves.  '
      comments:
      - number: '4:7 '
        content: Greek <b>We now have this treasure in clay jars.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'We are pressed on every side by troubles, but we are not crushed.
        We are perplexed, but not driven to despair. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are hunted down, but never abandoned by God. We get knocked down,
        but we are not destroyed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Through suffering, our bodies continue to share in the death of Jesus
        so that the life of Jesus may also be seen in our bodies.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, we live under constant danger of death because we serve Jesus,
        so that the life of Jesus will be evident in our dying bodies. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So we live in the face of death, but this has resulted in eternal
        life for you.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But we continue to preach because we have the same kind of faith
        the psalmist had when he said, \u201CI believed in God, so I spoke.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '4:13 '
        content: Ps 116:10.
    - title: 
      content: 'We know that God, who raised the Lord Jesus,[[COMMENT(0)]] will also
        raise us with Jesus and present us to himself together with you. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:14 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>who raised Jesus.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "All of this is for your benefit. And as God\u2019s grace reaches
        more and more people, there will be great thanksgiving, and God will receive
        more and more glory.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'That is why we never give up. Though our bodies are dying, our spirits
        are[[COMMENT(0)]] being renewed every day. '
      comments:
      - number: '4:16 '
        content: Greek <b>our inner being is.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "For our present troubles are small and won\u2019t last very long.
        Yet they produce for us a glory that vastly outweighs them and will last
        forever! "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: New Bodies
      content: '  For we know that when this earthly tent we live in is taken down
        (that is, when we die and leave this earthly body), we will have a house
        in heaven, an eternal body made for us by God himself and not by human hands. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We grow weary in our present bodies, and we long to put on our heavenly
        bodies like new clothing. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For we will put on heavenly bodies; we will not be spirits without
        bodies.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '5:3 '
        content: Greek <b>we will not be naked.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "While we live in these earthly bodies, we groan and sigh, but it\u2019s
        not that we want to die and get rid of these bodies that clothe us. Rather,
        we want to put on our new bodies so that these dying bodies will be swallowed
        up by life. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God himself has prepared us for this, and as a guarantee he has given
        us his Holy Spirit.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So we are always confident, even though we know that as long as we
        live in these bodies we are not at home with the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For we live by believing and not by seeing. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, we are fully confident, and we would rather be away from these
        earthly bodies, for then we will be at home with the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So whether we are here in this body or away from this body, our goal
        is to please him. '
      comments: []
    - title: "We Are God\u2019s Ambassadors"
      content: 'For we must all stand before Christ to be judged. We will each receive
        whatever we deserve for the good or evil we have done in this earthly body.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Because we understand our fearful responsibility to the Lord, we
        work hard to persuade others. God knows we are sincere, and I hope you know
        this, too. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Are we commending ourselves to you again? No, we are giving you a
        reason to be proud of us,[[COMMENT(0)]] so you can answer those who brag
        about having a spectacular ministry rather than having a sincere heart. '
      comments:
      - number: '5:12 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>proud of yourselves.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'If it seems we are crazy, it is to bring glory to God. And if we
        are in our right minds, it is for your benefit. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Either way, Christ\u2019s love controls us.[[COMMENT(0)]] Since we
        believe that Christ died for all, we also believe that we have all died to
        our old life.[[COMMENT(1)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '5:14a '
        content: Or <b>urges us on.</b>
      - number: '5:14b '
        content: Greek <b>Since one died for all, then all died.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'He died for everyone so that those who receive his new life will
        no longer live for themselves. Instead, they will live for Christ, who died
        and was raised for them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So we have stopped evaluating others from a human point of view.
        At one time we thought of Christ merely from a human point of view. How differently
        we know him now! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'This means that anyone who belongs to Christ has become a new person.
        The old life is gone; a new life has begun!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And all of this is a gift from God, who brought us back to himself
        through Christ. And God has given us this task of reconciling people to him. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For God was in Christ, reconciling the world to himself, no longer
        counting people\u2019s sins against them. And he gave us this wonderful message
        of reconciliation. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So we are Christ\u2019s ambassadors; God is making his appeal through
        us. We speak for Christ when we plead, \u201CCome back to God!\u201D "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: "  As God\u2019s partners,[[COMMENT(0)]] we beg you not to accept
        this marvelous gift of God\u2019s kindness and then ignore it. "
      comments:
      - number: '6:1 '
        content: Or <b>As we work together.</b>
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Hardships"
      content: "For God says,\u201CAt just the right time, I heard you.On the day
        of salvation, I helped you.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]Indeed, the \u201Cright time\u201D
        is now. Today is the day of salvation.  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:2 '
        content: Isa 49:8 (Greek version).
    - title: 
      content: 'We live in such a way that no one will stumble because of us, and
        no one will find fault with our ministry. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'In everything we do, we show that we are true ministers of God. We
        patiently endure troubles and hardships and calamities of every kind. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We have been beaten, been put in prison, faced angry mobs, worked
        to exhaustion, endured sleepless nights, and gone without food. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We prove ourselves by our purity, our understanding, our patience,
        our kindness, by the Holy Spirit within us,[[COMMENT(0)]] and by our sincere
        love. '
      comments:
      - number: '6:6 '
        content: Or <b>by our holiness of spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "We faithfully preach the truth. God\u2019s power is working in us.
        We use the weapons of righteousness in the right hand for attack and the
        left hand for defense. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We serve God whether people honor us or despise us, whether they
        slander us or praise us. We are honest, but they call us impostors. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are ignored, even though we are well known. We live close to death,
        but we are still alive. We have been beaten, but we have not been killed. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Our hearts ache, but we always have joy. We are poor, but we give
        spiritual riches to others. We own nothing, and yet we have everything.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Oh, dear Corinthian friends! We have spoken honestly with you, and
        our hearts are open to you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'There is no lack of love on our part, but you have withheld your
        love from us. '
      comments: []
    - title: The Temple of the Living God
      content: 'I am asking you to respond as if you were my own children. Open your
        hearts to us!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Don\u2019t team up with those who are unbelievers. How can righteousness
        be a partner with wickedness? How can light live with darkness? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'What harmony can there be between Christ and the devil[[COMMENT(0)]]?
        How can a believer be a partner with an unbeliever? '
      comments:
      - number: '6:15 '
        content: Greek <b>Beliar; </b>various other manuscripts render this proper
          name of the devil as <b>Belian, Beliab, </b>or <b>Belial.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "And what union can there be between God\u2019s temple and idols?
        For we are the temple of the living God. As God said:\u201CI will live in
        themand walk among them.I will be their God,and they will be my people.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:16 '
        content: Lev 26:12; Ezek 37:27.
    - title: 
      content: "Therefore, come out from among unbelievers,and separate yourselves
        from them, says the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.Don\u2019t touch their filthy
        things,and I will welcome you.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '6:17 '
        content: Isa 52:11; Ezek 20:34 (Greek version).
  - verses:
    - title: 
      content: '  Because we have these promises, dear friends, let us cleanse ourselves
        from everything that can defile our body or spirit. And let us work toward
        complete holiness because we fear God.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Please open your hearts to us. We have not done wrong to anyone,
        nor led anyone astray, nor taken advantage of anyone. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I\u2019m not saying this to condemn you. I said before that you are
        in our hearts, and we live or die together with you. "
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Joy at the Church\u2019s Repentance"
      content: 'I have the highest confidence in you, and I take great pride in you.
        You have greatly encouraged me and made me happy despite all our troubles.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When we arrived in Macedonia, there was no rest for us. We faced
        conflict from every direction, with battles on the outside and fear on the
        inside. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But God, who encourages those who are discouraged, encouraged us
        by the arrival of Titus. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'His presence was a joy, but so was the news he brought of the encouragement
        he received from you. When he told us how much you long to see me, and how
        sorry you are for what happened, and how loyal you are to me, I was filled
        with joy!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I am not sorry that I sent that severe letter to you, though I was
        sorry at first, for I know it was painful to you for a little while. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now I am glad I sent it, not because it hurt you, but because the
        pain caused you to repent and change your ways. It was the kind of sorrow
        God wants his people to have, so you were not harmed by us in any way. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For the kind of sorrow God wants us to experience leads us away from
        sin and results in salvation. There\u2019s no regret for that kind of sorrow.
        But worldly sorrow, which lacks repentance, results in spiritual death.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Just see what this godly sorrow produced in you! Such earnestness,
        such concern to clear yourselves, such indignation, such alarm, such longing
        to see me, such zeal, and such a readiness to punish wrong. You showed that
        you have done everything necessary to make things right. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'My purpose, then, was not to write about who did the wrong or who
        was wronged. I wrote to you so that in the sight of God you could see for
        yourselves how loyal you are to us. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We have been greatly encouraged by this.In addition to our own encouragement,
        we were especially delighted to see how happy Titus was about the way all
        of you welcomed him and set his mind[[COMMENT(0)]] at ease. '
      comments:
      - number: '7:13 '
        content: Greek <b>his spirit.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "I had told him how proud I was of you\u2014and you didn\u2019t disappoint
        me. I have always told you the truth, and now my boasting to Titus has also
        proved true! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now he cares for you more than ever when he remembers the way all
        of you obeyed him and welcomed him with such fear and deep respect. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: A Call to Generous Giving
      content: '  Now I want you to know, dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        what God in his kindness has done through the churches in Macedonia. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:1 '
        content: Greek <b>brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'They are being tested by many troubles, and they are very poor. But
        they are also filled with abundant joy, which has overflowed in rich generosity.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For I can testify that they gave not only what they could afford,
        but far more. And they did it of their own free will. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'They begged us again and again for the privilege of sharing in the
        gift for the believers in Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '8:4 '
        content: "Greek <b>for God\u2019s holy people.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'They even did more than we had hoped, for their first action was
        to give themselves to the Lord and to us, just as God wanted them to do.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So we have urged Titus, who encouraged your giving in the first place,
        to return to you and encourage you to finish this ministry of giving. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Since you excel in so many ways\u2014in your faith, your gifted speakers,
        your knowledge, your enthusiasm, and your love from us[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014I
        want you to excel also in this gracious act of giving.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:7 '
        content: Some manuscripts read <b>your love for us.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I am not commanding you to do this. But I am testing how genuine
        your love is by comparing it with the eagerness of the other churches.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You know the generous grace of our Lord Jesus Christ. Though he was
        rich, yet for your sakes he became poor, so that by his poverty he could
        make you rich.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Here is my advice: It would be good for you to finish what you started
        a year ago. Last year you were the first who wanted to give, and you were
        the first to begin doing it. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Now you should finish what you started. Let the eagerness you showed
        in the beginning be matched now by your giving. Give in proportion to what
        you have. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Whatever you give is acceptable if you give it eagerly. And give
        according to what you have, not what you don\u2019t have. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Of course, I don\u2019t mean your giving should make life easy for
        others and hard for yourselves. I only mean that there should be some equality. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Right now you have plenty and can help those who are in need. Later,
        they will have plenty and can share with you when you need it. In this way,
        things will be equal. '
      comments: []
    - title: Titus and His Companions
      content: "As the Scriptures say,\u201CThose who gathered a lot had nothing
        left over,and those who gathered only a little had enough.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:15 '
        content: Exod 16:18.
    - title: 
      content: 'But thank God! He has given Titus the same enthusiasm for you that
        I have. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Titus welcomed our request that he visit you again. In fact, he himself
        was very eager to go and see you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are also sending another brother with Titus. All the churches
        praise him as a preacher of the Good News. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "He was appointed by the churches to accompany us as we take the offering
        to Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]]\u2014a service that glorifies the Lord and shows
        our eagerness to help.  "
      comments:
      - number: '8:19 '
        content: See 1 Cor 16:3-4.
    - title: 
      content: 'We are traveling together to guard against any criticism for the
        way we are handling this generous gift. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are careful to be honorable before the Lord, but we also want
        everyone else to see that we are honorable.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are also sending with them another of our brothers who has proven
        himself many times and has shown on many occasions how eager he is. He is
        now even more enthusiastic because of his great confidence in you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If anyone asks about Titus, say that he is my partner who works with
        me to help you. And the brothers with him have been sent by the churches,[[COMMENT(0)]]
        and they bring honor to Christ. '
      comments:
      - number: '8:23 '
        content: Greek <b>are apostles of the churches.</b>
  - verses:
    - title: The Collection for Christians in Jerusalem
      content: "  I really don\u2019t need to write to you about this ministry of
        giving for the believers in Jerusalem.[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:1 '
        content: "Greek <b>about the offering for God\u2019s holy people.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'For I know how eager you are to help, and I have been boasting to
        the churches in Macedonia that you in Greece[[COMMENT(0)]] were ready to
        send an offering a year ago. In fact, it was your enthusiasm that stirred
        up many of the Macedonian believers to begin giving.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:2 '
        content: Greek <b>in Achaia, </b>the southern region of the Greek peninsula.
          <b>Macedonia </b>was in the northern region of Greece.
    - title: 
      content: "But I am sending these brothers to be sure you really are ready,
        as I have been telling them, and that your money is all collected. I don\u2019t
        want to be wrong in my boasting about you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We would be embarrassed\u2014not to mention your own embarrassment\u2014if
        some Macedonian believers came with me and found that you weren\u2019t ready
        after all I had told them! "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'So I thought I should send these brothers ahead of me to make sure
        the gift you promised is ready. But I want it to be a willing gift, not one
        given grudgingly.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Remember this\u2014a farmer who plants only a few seeds will get
        a small crop. But the one who plants generously will get a generous crop. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You must each decide in your heart how much to give. And don\u2019t
        give reluctantly or in response to pressure. \u201CFor God loves a person
        who gives cheerfully.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:7 '
        content: See footnote on Prov 22:8.
    - title: 
      content: 'And God will generously provide all you need. Then you will always
        have everything you need and plenty left over to share with others. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As the Scriptures say,\u201CThey share freely and give generously
        to the poor.Their good deeds will be remembered forever.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:9 '
        content: Ps 112:9.
    - title: 
      content: 'For God is the one who provides seed for the farmer and then bread
        to eat. In the same way, he will provide and increase your resources and
        then produce a great harvest of generosity[[COMMENT(0)]] in you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '9:10 '
        content: Greek <b>righteousness.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, you will be enriched in every way so that you can always be
        generous. And when we take your gifts to those who need them, they will thank
        God. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "So two good things will result from this ministry of giving\u2014the
        needs of the believers in Jerusalem[[COMMENT(0)]] will be met, and they will
        joyfully express their thanks to God.  "
      comments:
      - number: '9:12 '
        content: "Greek <b>of God\u2019s holy people.</b>"
    - title: 
      content: 'As a result of your ministry, they will give glory to God. For your
        generosity to them and to all believers will prove that you are obedient
        to the Good News of Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And they will pray for you with deep affection because of the overflowing
        grace God has given to you. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: Paul Defends His Authority
      content: "  Now I, Paul, appeal to you with the gentleness and kindness of
        Christ\u2014though I realize you think I am timid in person and bold only
        when I write from far away. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Well, I am begging you now so that when I come I won\u2019t have
        to be bold with those who think we act from human motives.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We are human, but we don\u2019t wage war as humans do. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "[[COMMENT(0)]]We use God\u2019s mighty weapons, not worldly weapons,
        to knock down the strongholds of human reasoning and to destroy false arguments. "
      comments:
      - number: '10:4 '
        content: English translations divide verses 4 and 5 in various ways.
    - title: 
      content: 'We destroy every proud obstacle that keeps people from knowing God.
        We capture their rebellious thoughts and teach them to obey Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And after you have become fully obedient, we will punish everyone
        who remains disobedient.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Look at the obvious facts.[[COMMENT(0)]] Those who say they belong
        to Christ must recognize that we belong to Christ as much as they do. '
      comments:
      - number: '10:7 '
        content: Or <b>You look at things only on the basis of appearance.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "I may seem to be boasting too much about the authority given to us
        by the Lord. But our authority builds you up; it doesn\u2019t tear you down.
        So I will not be ashamed of using my authority.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I\u2019m not trying to frighten you by my letters. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For some say, \u201CPaul\u2019s letters are demanding and forceful,
        but in person he is weak, and his speeches are worthless!\u201D "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Those people should realize that our actions when we arrive in person
        will be as forceful as what we say in our letters from far away.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Oh, don\u2019t worry; we wouldn\u2019t dare say that we are as wonderful
        as these other men who tell you how important they are! But they are only
        comparing themselves with each other, using themselves as the standard of
        measurement. How ignorant!  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We will not boast about things done outside our area of authority.
        We will boast only about what has happened within the boundaries of the work
        God has given us, which includes our working with you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are not reaching beyond these boundaries when we claim authority
        over you, as if we had never visited you. For we were the first to travel
        all the way to Corinth with the Good News of Christ.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Nor do we boast and claim credit for the work someone else has done.
        Instead, we hope that your faith will grow so that the boundaries of our
        work among you will be extended. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Then we will be able to go and preach the Good News in other places
        far beyond you, where no one else is working. Then there will be no question
        of our boasting about work done in someone else\u2019s territory. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "As the Scriptures say, \u201CIf you want to boast, boast only about
        the <smallcaps>Lord</smallcaps>.\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]  "
      comments:
      - number: '10:17 '
        content: Jer 9:24.
  - verses:
    - title: Paul and the False Apostles
      content: '  I hope you will put up with a little more of my foolishness. Please
        bear with me. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I am jealous for you with the jealousy of God himself. I promised
        you as a pure bride[[COMMENT(0)]] to one husband\u2014Christ. "
      comments:
      - number: '11:2 '
        content: Greek <b>a virgin.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'But I fear that somehow your pure and undivided devotion to Christ
        will be corrupted, just as Eve was deceived by the cunning ways of the serpent. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You happily put up with whatever anyone tells you, even if they preach
        a different Jesus than the one we preach, or a different kind of Spirit than
        the one you received, or a different kind of gospel than the one you believed.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "But I don\u2019t consider myself inferior in any way to these \u201Csuper
        apostles\u201D who teach such things. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I may be unskilled as a speaker, but I\u2019m not lacking in knowledge.
        We have made this clear to you in every possible way.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Was I wrong when I humbled myself and honored you by preaching God\u2019s
        Good News to you without expecting anything in return? "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I \u201Crobbed\u201D other churches by accepting their contributions
        so I could serve you at no cost. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "And when I was with you and didn\u2019t have enough to live on, I
        did not become a financial burden to anyone. For the brothers who came from
        Macedonia brought me all that I needed. I have never been a burden to you,
        and I never will be. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'As surely as the truth of Christ is in me, no one in all of Greece[[COMMENT(0)]]
        will ever stop me from boasting about this. '
      comments:
      - number: '11:10 '
        content: Greek <b>Achaia, </b>the southern region of the Greek peninsula.
    - title: 
      content: "Why? Because I don\u2019t love you? God knows that I do.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I will continue doing what I have always done. This will undercut
        those who are looking for an opportunity to boast that their work is just
        like ours. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'These people are false apostles. They are deceitful workers who disguise
        themselves as apostles of Christ. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But I am not surprised! Even Satan disguises himself as an angel
        of light. '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Many Trials"
      content: 'So it is no wonder that his servants also disguise themselves as
        servants of righteousness. In the end they will get the punishment their
        wicked deeds deserve.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Again I say, don\u2019t think that I am a fool to talk like this.
        But even if you do, listen to me, as you would to a foolish person, while
        I also boast a little. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Such boasting is not from the Lord, but I am acting like a fool. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'And since others boast about their human achievements, I will, too. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'After all, you think you are so wise, but you enjoy putting up with
        fools! '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'You put up with it when someone enslaves you, takes everything you
        have, takes advantage of you, takes control of everything, and slaps you
        in the face. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I\u2019m ashamed to say that we\u2019ve been too \u201Cweak\u201D
        to do that!But whatever they dare to boast about\u2014I\u2019m talking like
        a fool again\u2014I dare to boast about it, too. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Are they Hebrews? So am I. Are they Israelites? So am I. Are they
        descendants of Abraham? So am I. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Are they servants of Christ? I know I sound like a madman, but I
        have served him far more! I have worked harder, been put in prison more often,
        been whipped times without number, and faced death again and again. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Five different times the Jewish leaders gave me thirty-nine lashes. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Three times I was beaten with rods. Once I was stoned. Three times
        I was shipwrecked. Once I spent a whole night and a day adrift at sea. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I have traveled on many long journeys. I have faced danger from rivers
        and from robbers. I have faced danger from my own people, the Jews, as well
        as from the Gentiles. I have faced danger in the cities, in the deserts,
        and on the seas. And I have faced danger from men who claim to be believers
        but are not.[[COMMENT(0)]]  '
      comments:
      - number: '11:26 '
        content: Greek <b>from false brothers.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'I have worked hard and long, enduring many sleepless nights. I have
        been hungry and thirsty and have often gone without food. I have shivered
        in the cold, without enough clothing to keep me warm.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Then, besides all this, I have the daily burden of my concern for
        all the churches. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Who is weak without my feeling that weakness? Who is led astray,
        and I do not burn with anger?  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'If I must boast, I would rather boast about the things that show
        how weak I am. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'God, the Father of our Lord Jesus, who is worthy of eternal praise,
        knows I am not lying. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When I was in Damascus, the governor under King Aretas kept guards
        at the city gates to catch me. '
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Vision and His Thorn in the Flesh"
      content: '  This boasting will do no good, but I must go on. I will reluctantly
        tell about visions and revelations from the Lord. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "I[[COMMENT(0)]] was caught up to the third heaven fourteen years
        ago. Whether I was in my body or out of my body, I don\u2019t know\u2014only
        God knows. "
      comments:
      - number: '12:2 '
        content: Greek <b>I know a man in Christ who.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'Yes, only God knows whether I was in my body or outside my body.
        But I do know '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'that I was caught up[[COMMENT(0)]] to paradise and heard things so
        astounding that they cannot be expressed in words, things no human is allowed
        to tell.  '
      comments:
      - number: '12:3-4 '
        content: Greek <b>But I know such a man, </b><b>that he was caught up.</b>
    - title: 
      content: "That experience is worth boasting about, but I\u2019m not going to
        do it. I will boast only about my weaknesses. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "If I wanted to boast, I would be no fool in doing so, because I would
        be telling the truth. But I won\u2019t do it, because I don\u2019t want anyone
        to give me credit beyond what they can see in my life or hear in my message, "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'even though I have received such wonderful revelations from God.
        So to keep me from becoming proud, I was given a thorn in my flesh, a messenger
        from Satan to torment me and keep me from becoming proud.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Three different times I begged the Lord to take it away. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Each time he said, \u201CMy grace is all you need. My power works
        best in weakness.\u201D So now I am glad to boast about my weaknesses, so
        that the power of Christ can work through me. "
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Concern for the Corinthians"
      content: "That\u2019s why I take pleasure in my weaknesses, and in the insults,
        hardships, persecutions, and troubles that I suffer for Christ. For when
        I am weak, then I am strong.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "You have made me act like a fool. You ought to be writing commendations
        for me, for I am not at all inferior to these \u201Csuper apostles,\u201D
        even though I am nothing at all. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'When I was with you, I certainly gave you proof that I am an apostle.
        For I patiently did many signs and wonders and miracles among you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'The only thing I failed to do, which I do in the other churches,
        was to become a financial burden to you. Please forgive me for this wrong!  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Now I am coming to you for the third time, and I will not be a burden
        to you. I don\u2019t want what you have\u2014I want you. After all, children
        don\u2019t provide for their parents. Rather, parents provide for their children. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will gladly spend myself and all I have for you, even though it
        seems that the more I love you, the less you love me.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Some of you admit I was not a burden to you. But others still think
        I was sneaky and took advantage of you by trickery. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'But how? Did any of the men I sent to you take advantage of you? '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "When I urged Titus to visit you and sent our other brother with him,
        did Titus take advantage of you? No! For we have the same spirit and walk
        in each other\u2019s steps, doing things the same way.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Perhaps you think we\u2019re saying these things just to defend ourselves.
        No, we tell you this as Christ\u2019s servants, and with God as our witness.
        Everything we do, dear friends, is to strengthen you. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "For I am afraid that when I come I won\u2019t like what I find, and
        you won\u2019t like my response. I am afraid that I will find quarreling,
        jealousy, anger, selfishness, slander, gossip, arrogance, and disorderly
        behavior. "
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Final Advice"
      content: "  This is the third time I am coming to visit you (and as the Scriptures
        say, \u201CThe facts of every case must be established by the testimony of
        two or three witnesses\u201D[[COMMENT(0)]]). "
      comments:
      - number: '13:1 '
        content: Deut 19:15.
    - title: 
      content: 'I have already warned those who had been sinning when I was there
        on my second visit. Now I again warn them and all others, just as I did before,
        that next time I will not spare them.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'I will give you all the proof you want that Christ speaks through
        me. Christ is not weak when he deals with you; he is powerful among you. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "Although he was crucified in weakness, he now lives by the power
        of God. We, too, are weak, just as Christ was, but when we deal with you
        we will be alive with him and will have God\u2019s power.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Examine yourselves to see if your faith is genuine. Test yourselves.
        Surely you know that Jesus Christ is among you[[COMMENT(0)]]; if not, you
        have failed the test of genuine faith. '
      comments:
      - number: '13:5 '
        content: Or <b>in you.</b>
    - title: 
      content: 'As you test yourselves, I hope you will recognize that we have not
        failed the test of apostolic authority.  '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "We pray to God that you will not do what is wrong by refusing our
        correction. I hope we won\u2019t need to demonstrate our authority when we
        arrive. Do the right thing before we come\u2014even if that makes it look
        like we have failed to demonstrate our authority. "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'For we cannot oppose the truth, but must always stand for the truth. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'We are glad to seem weak if it helps show that you are actually strong.
        We pray that you will become mature.  '
      comments: []
    - title: "Paul\u2019s Final Greetings"
      content: "I am writing this to you before I come, hoping that I won\u2019t
        need to deal severely with you when I do come. For I want to use the authority
        the Lord has given me to strengthen you, not to tear you down.  "
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: 'Dear brothers and sisters,[[COMMENT(0)]] I close my letter with these
        last words: Be joyful. Grow to maturity. Encourage each other. Live in harmony
        and peace. Then the God of love and peace will be with you.  '
      comments:
      - number: '13:11 '
        content: 'Greek <b>Brothers.</b>  '
    - title: 
      content: 'Greet each other with a sacred kiss. '
      comments: []
    - title: 
      content: "All of God\u2019s people here send you their greetings.  "
      comments: []
